    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-23T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-23T11:00:00-05:00" n="702"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d702">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">600.0031 World Program/197: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-23T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 23, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 23—12:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>68. My telegram No. 66, August 12, 10 a.m.<note n="25" xml:id="d702fn25">Not
                        printed.</note> Frère tells me that we need expect no further developments
                    for several weeks. The Prime Minister has come to the conclusion that it would
                    be desirable to have some form of agenda, however general, before undertaking
                    the conversations referred to in the draft note.<note n="26" xml:id="d702fn26"
                        >Memorandum dated July 17, <ref target="#pg_684">p. 684</ref>.</note> In his
                    opinion it is better to await the conclusion of the discussions which will take
                    place in Geneva in September concerning raw materials,<note n="27"
                        xml:id="d702fn27">See <ref target="#pg_803">pp. 803</ref> ff.</note> etc.,
                    before trying to determine what should be embodied in this agenda. I, therefore,
                    doubt whether any further steps will be taken before the end of September.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
